@* Root Razor Component for the WopiHost.Web frontend. Per the .NET 10 Minimal-API +
   Razor Components idiom, App.razor owns the <html>/<head>/<body> structure and the
   <Routes> child renders into <body>. Static SSR — no @rendermode set, so each request
   returns plain pre-rendered HTML and the sample stays a thin viewer without SignalR.

   Stylesheets live here (NOT in MainLayout's <HeadContent>) because page-level <HeadContent>
   in static SSR replaces — not merges with — the layout's <HeadContent>. Anything every page
   needs (marx-css, site.css) goes in this root <head> so it's always present. WopiLayout's
   own inline styles (body{margin:0;...} + #office_frame at 100%) cover marx-css visually on
   the editor host page, so it doesn't matter that the styles also load there. *@

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <base href="/" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/marx-css/css/marx.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/site.css" />
    <HeadOutlet />
</head>
<body>
    <Routes />
</body>
</html>
